BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:BMDLQpJm5aE78l8PubPjP
SUMMARY:Anila Quayyum Agha: Geometry of Light
DTSTAMP:20260321T020253Z
DTSTART:20260401T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Anila Quayyum Agha: Geometry of Light invites you to become par
	t of the art. Agha\, a Pakistani American artist\, animates spaces with he
	r large-scale sculptural installations. Suspended from the ceiling\, Agha’
	s steel cubes are laser-cut with intricate designs that project geometric 
	shadows onto the visitor. She draws on both the light and dark of her own 
	life\, using South Asian art practices to convey the gender discrimination
	 she faced growing up as a young girl in Pakistan. An in-depth exploration
	 of Islamic architecture\, art\, and identity\, this is the first solo exh
	ibition of a Pakistani American artist in SAM’s 90-year history. Agha is c
	arving a name out for herself in the art world—visit the Seattle Asian Art
	 Museum for an immersive and illuminating experience.\n\nhttps://seatoday.
	6amcity.com/events/#/details/anila-quayyum-agha-geometry-of-light/16795597
	/2026-04-01T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/anila-quayyum-agha-geomet
	ry-of-light/16795597/2026-04-01T00
LOCATION:Seattle Art Museum\, 1300 First Avenue\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-arts
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT7H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:TtWFt8UdrT3cN4gTAjGCI
SUMMARY:Small Frye: Storytelling + Art
DTSTAMP:20260321T020253Z
DTSTART:20260401T171500Z
DESCRIPTION:Registration will open approximately a month before the event. 
	Enjoy a lively retelling of a beloved children’s book\, then create art wi
	th loved ones using materials designed to spark tactile play and wonder. T
	he hands-on art activity\, inspired by "Priscilla Dobler Dzul: Water Carri
	es the Stories of Our Stars\," is designed to enhance the skills and devel
	opmental strengths of pre-K children in collaboration with their caregiver
	s. This Small Frye session features the picture book Goldilocks and the Th
	ree Dinosaurs by Mo Willems.  Small Frye is free\, but registration is req
	uired. Space is limited—sign up today! --- https://fryemuseum.org/calendar
	/event/small-frye-april-2026\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/deta
	ils/small-frye-storytelling-art/16963158/2026-04-01T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - 
	Arts & Culture
